articles.title: Humanoid robots are on the march. Here are some of the most eyebrow-raising demo videos out there right now.
articles.summary: Realbotix introduced Aria, an AI-powered humanoid robot designed for companionship. Clone Robotics released a video of its Protoclone synthetic humanoid robot featuring artificial muscles. 1X Robotics showcased its NEO Gamma robot designed for household chores like tidying and home management.

articles.title: Aldi is selling a huge 9litre air fryer that's 283% cheaper than Ninja
articles.author: Freya Parsons
articles.summary: Aldi is launching the Dual Zone Air Fryer for £64.99 on March 2nd, featuring two drawers, an LED touchscreen, and 10 programs.  Additionally, Aldi will release the 4.8-litre Ambiano Air Fryer With Window for £39.99, alongside other kitchen Specialbuys, including a Stir Fry Wok, a Multi-Function Chopper, Pancake Pan Assortment and Air Fryer Accessories.

articles.title: 6 solid Samsung Galaxy A16 5G features that are hard to find in other budget phones
articles.author: Sanuj Bhatia
articles.summary: Samsung has launched the Galaxy A16 5G, a budget smartphone featuring a 6.7-inch Super AMOLED display, IP54 rating for dust and water resistance, and 128GB base storage. The Galaxy A16 5G also includes a 50MP primary camera, 5,000mAh battery with 25W fast charging, and a commitment to six years of software updates.

articles.title: 35 Beauty Products You'll Honestly Be Mad You Didn't Know About Before Now
articles.author: Emma Lord
articles.summary: Several beauty companies have introduced new products, including Olay with its Super Serum Body Wash containing niacinamide, shea butter, and collagen peptides, and Laneige with its Neo Blurring Powder designed to absorb oil and blur pores. E.l.f. launched the Lash XTNDR Tubing Mascara with tubing technology for natural-looking lash extension.  These launches feature various products from different brands, highlighting innovations and their intended benefits.

articles.title: The Yellow Deli now open, following health dept. approval
articles.author: SCOTT JOHNSON
articles.summary: The Yellow Deli in Mobile has officially opened a new restaurant, offering steamed sandwiches, soups, and baked goods. The restaurant has been serving guests since January 29th, operating from 7 a.m. to 3 p.m., Sunday through Friday.

articles.title: 10 Things That Delighted Us: From a New Status Hand Soap to Jennifer Aniston's Screen Cleaner
articles.author: The Editors
articles.summary: The article highlights recent product favorites, including the tinyPod, an Apple Watch case resembling a classic iPod.  Loewe's Tomato Leaves soap is identified as a popular choice in restaurants and hotels.  Béis suitcases were gifted by gymnast Jordan Chiles, and CB2 launched a limited-edition collection inspired by the show 'White Lotus' luxe hotel chain.

articles.title: Why is everyone ditching their iPhones for this mini smartphone?
articles.author: Stack Commerce
articles.summary: The NanoPhone, a mini smartphone, is being launched and offered for sale at $99.97 with free shipping until February 23. It supports existing 4G plans via SIM card and functions like a standard Android phone, making it a suitable primary or backup device.

articles.title: Silicon Valley is going all in on humanoid robots. Making them a reality will take decades.
articles.author: Daniel Howley
articles.summary: Amazon, Google, Microsoft, Nvidia, Tesla, Meta, and Apple are investing in humanoid robotics systems.  The article mentions specific robots like Tesla's Optimus, Agility AI's Digit, and Figure AI's 02. These robots will be able to perform more specialized tasks using hands that can grab and grip without crushing objects.

articles.title: Woolworths launch Cinnabon hot cross buns ahead of Easter
articles.author: Zoe De Koning
articles.summary: Woolworths is launching a new Cinnabon hot cross bun flavour in collaboration with Cinnabon. This product features Cinnabon cinnamon flavour and a cream cheese-style filling and will be available in Woolworths supermarkets this Friday. This launch follows successful collaborations with Biscoff and Fairy Bread flavours in previous years.

articles.title: 65 Weird Things For Women That Are Pure Genius
articles.author: Caroline Reinstadtler
articles.summary: BOLDIFY introduced a dry texture spray designed to add volume and texture to hair without the stiffness of traditional hairsprays, suitable for all hair types and even second-day hair. Additionally, Nelko launched a label maker machine with Bluetooth connectivity and a companion app, enabling users to create customized labels with pictures, fonts, and QR codes using thermal printing technology.

articles.title: NEO Gamma: the humanoid robot that does all house chores and recharges itself
articles.author: Al Bawaba
articles.summary: A company (unnamed in the content) introduces NEO Gamma, a new humanoid. This product launch fulfills a long-held aspiration for many.

articles.title: NEO Gamma: the humanoid robot that does all house chores and recharges itself
articles.summary: 1X Technologies introduced NEO Gamma, a new humanoid robot designed for household chores. The robot can clean, arrange items, wash clothes and dishes, and prepare food. It will also recharge itself and is expected to cost around $30,000.

articles.title: Unhappy with your Instagram reach? Here's how to boost it using AI tools like ChatGPT
articles.author: Tech Desk
articles.summary: ChatGPT, an AI tool, can enhance Instagram post reach by crafting engaging captions, optimizing keywords, selecting hashtags, and brainstorming content ideas. Users can provide text or image prompts to ChatGPT for personalized assistance to improve the reach of their instagram posts.

articles.title: Krispy Kreme Belfast opening hours for first Northern Irish store
articles.author: Sophie McLaughlin
articles.summary: Krispy Kreme is opening its first store in Northern Ireland, located in Victoria Square Belfast, on March 12th at 8 am. The store will offer their iconic Original Glazed doughnuts, seasonal flavors, coffees, shakes, and soft drinks. The Belfast launch is the first of a series of planned openings in Northern Ireland.

articles.title: Ooredoo Expands Retail Footprint with New Franchise Store at Lulu Al Ansab
articles.summary: Ooredoo has opened a new franchise kiosk at Lulu Hypermarket in Al Ansab to enhance customer convenience and experience. The kiosk offers prepaid and postpaid plans, high-speed internet solutions, exclusive offers, and customer support, providing access to Ooredoo products and services.

articles.title: I love Sky's new mega TV but popular Q box still has a certain advantage – and there's a cheaper option coming soon
articles.author: Jamie Harris
articles.summary: Sky has launched Sky Glass Gen 2, an upgraded version of its integrated TV. Key improvements include enhanced visuals, better audio with seven speakers, and an easier setup process. The Sky Glass Gen 2 retains the same pricing structure as the previous model, starting from £14 per month, and is primarily targeted at new Sky Glass customers.

articles.title: I love Sky's new mega TV but popular Q box still has a certain advantage – and there's a cheaper option coming soon
articles.author: Jamie Harris
articles.summary: Sky has launched Sky Glass Gen 2, an upgraded version of its internet-based streaming TV, with improvements in display, sound, and setup. The new Sky Glass Gen 2 is available in three sizes: 43-inch, 55-inch and 65-inch. It features an improved UHD Quantum Dot display, better sound system with seven speakers, and an easier setup process compared to its predecessor. The Sky Glass Gen 2 prices start from £14 per month.

articles.title: $20K foldable tiny home in a box you can set up in just 1 hour
articles.author: Kurt Knutsson
articles.summary: Boxabl introduces the 'Baby Box,' an innovative, foldable, ultra-compact home designed for easy setup and mobility. This fully functional living space features a multipurpose sofa-bed, a kitchen equipped with appliances and USB outlets, and a bathroom with a marine-style toilet and glass-enclosed shower.

articles.title: Asus will sell a mouse that's also an aromatic oil diffuser
articles.author: Nadeem Sarwar
articles.summary: Asus has officially announced the Fragrance Mouse as a standalone product, initially showcased at CES. The mouse, featuring a compartment for aromatic oils, is set to be released in Asus's home market and is coming to the US.

articles.title: MEF's TWO Milestones: NaaS Network APIs (MWC Demo) & Ninth LSO API release
articles.summary: MEF, in partnership with GSMA, Colt, and Orange, is debuting NaaS Network APIs for an AI-Driven Economy at MWC 2025, showcasing real-time 'Quality on Demand' capabilities powered by CAMARA APIs. Colt's On-Demand NaaS platform is ensuring dynamic service quality across the core backbone network and Orange's 5G Quality on Demand capability is optimizing mobile network performance. MEF's Ninth LSO API Release enhances service provider and enterprise automation adoption with advanced addressing capabilities, operational observability, and expanded service payloads.

articles.title: Beauty device gives users 'softer legs' in 'weeks' without waxing and it's now £140 off
articles.author: Lucy Addicott
articles.summary: Keskine recently launched the IPL Hair Removal Handset, priced at £199, promising a 98% hair reduction in four weeks. The device features ice-cooling technology and multiple modes for different body parts. Keskine offers a 90-day money back guarantee and an additional 20% discount with the code LASER20.

articles.title: New Marks & Spencer's 'sophisticated-looking top' for £20 doesn't need ironing
articles.author: Husna Anjum
articles.summary: Marks & Spencer is offering a new Short Sleeve Textured Top designed in a regular fit, available in sizes 6-24 and multiple colors. Shoppers praise its sophisticated look and no-iron feature. Next also offers a crafted sleeveless tank top.

articles.title: Asus is making a ‘Fragrance Mouse,' and it's coming to the US
articles.author: archyde
articles.summary: Asus is launching the Fragrance Mouse, a new peripheral that diffuses scent through a refillable vial of essential oils. Designed to work with any Bluetooth or 2.4GHz USB dongle-compatible device, it will be available in the US around late April, early May as an affordable luxury, according to Asus' Innovation Lead, Dr. Amina Hart.

articles.title: Asus reveals a new line of mice with the strangest feature I've ever seen
articles.author: Simon Batt
articles.summary: Asus has launched the ASUS Fragrance Mouse, a stylish and ergonomic mouse available in Iridescent White or Rose Clay finishes. It features an internal fragrance compartment with a refillable vial for aromatic oils, PTFE feet, adjustable DPI, durable switches with a 10-million-click lifespan, and dual-mode connectivity with 2.4GHz wireless and Bluetooth technologies.

articles.title: 28 Walmart Travel Products That Will Make You Feel Like A Genius
articles.author: Cierra Cowan
articles.summary: Walmart is offering a variety of new travel-related products. These products include a lightweight silicone water bottle, phone stand, adhesive phone wallet pouch, Poo-Pourri pocket sprayer, portable door lock, handheld fan, Apple AirTags, Tide-To-Go pen, adjustable memory foam neck pillow, portable charging bank, waterproof phone pouch, Bluetooth sleep headband, portable booster pack, leather passport holder, foldable packing cubes, handheld steamer, travel-size dry shampoo, LifeStraw, Sea Band acupressure wristband, Revlon 2-in-1 hair styling tool, Bluetooth transmitter, digital luggage scale, soap sheets, universal power plug adaptor, travel-size weekly pill organizer, infinity scarf, hooded rain poncho and Lumify eye drops. The products aim to improve travel experiences with their usefulness.

articles.title: How great is the Send Later feature?
articles.author: Nicolas Magand
articles.summary: Slack and Apple Messages offer a 'send later' feature which allows users to delay sending messages. This feature is highlighted as a valuable tool that caters to busy schedules and facilitates thoughtful communication.

articles.title: Meghan Markle trying to prove one thing with new brand launch
articles.author: Lauren Welch
articles.summary: Meghan Markle launched her new brand, As Ever. The brand signifies her return to business ventures, potentially mirroring her career before joining the Royal Family. Harry is unlikely to be heavily involved, and Meghan aims to demonstrate her independence as a businesswoman.

articles.title: New Tesla Model Y Arrive At Los Angeles Store Ahead Of Deliveries
articles.author: archyde
articles.summary: The new Tesla Model Y has started arriving at a Tesla store in North Hollywood, Los Angeles. Less expensive versions of the Model Y are available for order in Europe, starting at approximately 46,000 Euros. A test drive of the Model Y with v13 of Full Self Driving was conducted, showing improvements in the self-driving capabilities.

articles.title: CLIFTONIA: THE LAUNCH OF ELON'S MUSK
articles.author: Farid Alvie
articles.summary: The House of Cliftonia has launched a new perfume called "Elon's Musk". The perfume's launch has generated significant attention, receiving endorsements from prominent figures and sparking both enthusiasm and controversy. Orders for the perfume are pouring in from various segments of society.

articles.title: New complete set for men and women unveiled
articles.author: The Star
articles.summary: TaylorMade has launched the RBZ Complete set, presenting a new experience to its customers. The company describes the RBZ as a 'total package'.

articles.title: Leaked hands-on Samsung Galaxy S25 Edge video hints at its design and specs – and ...
articles.author: Tech Radar
articles.summary: Samsung's Galaxy S25 Edge handset was briefly seen, suggesting ongoing development or nearing release.

articles.title: From ‘what if' to ‘what next?'
articles.author: Irish Independent
articles.summary: Bánór, a bodycare brand, is introducing online delivery.

articles.title: Doha Bank launches digital account opening via Mobile Banking app
articles.author: Gulf-Times
articles.summary: Doha Bank has launched a new digital account opening feature available through its mobile banking application. This service enables customers to open bank accounts directly from their smartphones.

articles.title: Designing smart cities, fulfilling mid-career dreams: How they found their purpose through an arts degree
articles.author: Straits Times
articles.summary: Google launched Gemini Pro, an AI platform, at a developer launch event.

articles.title: One of my favorite foldables brings the flip phone back in the best way (and ...
articles.author: ZDNet
articles.summary: Samsung is launching the Galaxy Z Flip 6. The new phone features notable upgrades across the board.

articles.title: Prebiotic sodas: What are they, and why are they everywhere?
articles.author: The Hill
articles.summary: Poppi and Olipop, startups dedicated to prebiotic soda, have launched in the last decade and gained popularity. These brands target wellness-focused Gen Z and Millennial consumers with colorful and trendy prebiotic sodas.
